I'm getting errors on macOS Sierra 10.12 as well
`src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:59:29: error: use of undeclared identifier

      destructor
ServerBuilder::~ServerBuilder() {

      'resource_quota_'
  if (resource_quota_ != nullptr) {

src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:80:31: error: use of undeclared identifier
      'resource_quota_'
    grpc_resource_quota_unref(resource_quota_);

src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:122:20: error: no type named 'SyncServerOption' in
      'grpc::ServerBuilder'
    ServerBuilder::SyncServerOption option, int val) {
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^
src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:163:31: error: out-of-line definition of
      'SetResourceQuota' does not match any declaration in 'grpc::ServerBuilder'
ServerBuilder& ServerBuilder::SetResourceQuota(
                              ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:165:7: error: use of undeclared identifier
      'resource_quota_'; did you mean 'resource_quota'?
  if (resource_quota_ != nullptr) {
      ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      resource_quota
src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:164:32: note: 'resource_quota' declared here
    const grpc::ResourceQuota& resource_quota) {
                               ^
src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:165:23: error: invalid operands to binary
      expression ('const grpc::ResourceQuota' and 'nullptr_t')
  if (resource_quota_ != nullptr) {
      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ ^  ~~~~~~~
/usr/local/include/grpc++/impl/codegen/string_ref.h:149:13: note: candidate
      function not viable: no known conversion from 'const grpc::ResourceQuota' to
      'grpc::string_ref' for 1st argument
inline bool operator!=(string_ref x, string_ref y) { return x.compare(y) != 0; }
            ^
src/cpp/server/server_builder.cc:166:31: error: use of undeclared identifier
      'resource_quota_'
    grpc_resource_quota_unref(resource_quota_);
                              ^`
I get the same error ! if you fix it please tell me how !

i got the same error. 
but '/usr/bin/libtool' works fine.


Has anyone found a solution to this issue? I'm getting this on Sierra 10.12.6. I'm using libtool 2.4.6_1 through brew. libtool 2.4.6 doesn't seem to support the -no_warning_for_no_symbols option.
on the osx, i have installed gnu libtool via homebrew,  but we should use osx libtool /usr/bin/libtool to instead.
